      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "31076261_ce5da89c",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 38,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-24T23:26:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s a good idea. However, NewSectionReader() doesn\u0027t implement Close(), and, therefore, http.Client.Do() won\u0027t close req.Body when it finished the transmission.\n\nI tried to add Close() into io.SectionReader by embedding or aliasing it into a new struct, but couldn\u0027t find a super nice way of doing it without introducing a new field to keep the original mmap handler. I will play more with it and send a CL, if I could make it work.",
      "parentUuid": "e799d554_44b54909",
