      },
      "lineNbr": 116,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-25T01:06:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "oops. your are 100% right. fixed with `defer input.Close()`",
      "parentUuid": "9b79b995_0e80ade7",
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "92c652b8_91ceb671",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 121,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-24T06:01:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "from https://godoc.org/net/http#Request.GetBody\n\n\u003e Use of GetBody still requires setting Body.",
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a1ebc77e_3f33a2d3",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 121,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-24T23:26:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "At L117, `input` is passed to u.newRequest, and at L56, NewRequestWithContext() takes a param `body`, which is set the `Body` of the created request.\n\nhttps://golang.org/src/net/http/request.go#L877\nNewRequestWithContext installs GetBody() by itself, if it\u0027s one of bytes.{Buffer,Reader} and strings.Reader. In ArtifactUploader{}, GetBody() is required for an artifact from a file input only.",
      "parentUuid": "92c652b8_91ceb671",
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7adb6fee_508afd7d",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 122,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-24T06:01:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hmm, why are we reopening the same file? why not seek?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 122,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 122,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "101905d3_6efdf301",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 122,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-24T18:21:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Unfortunately the semantics of GetBody aren\u0027t clearly documented; I tried to read the docs to see if seek would be a sensible thing to do, but my read is that http has the right to close Body before calling GetBody again; in that case we would have to reopen the file.",
      "parentUuid": "7adb6fee_508afd7d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 122,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 122,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "89b38644_d9047198",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 122,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-24T23:26:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As Robbie mentioned, the doc doesn\u0027t seem to clearly describe whether Client.Do() would close the request body on 3xx response before looping back to the beginning, but the current implementation does so.\n\nAt https://golang.org/src/net/http/client.go#L718, Client.Do() closes the request body, and then loops back to the beginning, if the response was sent with 3xx status code.",
      "parentUuid": "101905d3_6efdf301",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 122,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 122,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4b57512c_58bcea52",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 122,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-24T23:41:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "it would be simpler to use ioutil.NopCloser(theFile) as body to avoid this unclarity?",
      "parentUuid": "89b38644_d9047198",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 122,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 122,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4880e1a7_b6496631",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 122,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-25T01:06:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s a good idea. It actually solves the problem of using mmap()-ed file. If UploadFromFile() self-closes the body on return, then it\u0027s no longer necessary to add and implement Close() on SectionReader.\n\nDone. PTAL",
      "parentUuid": "4b57512c_58bcea52",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 122,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 122,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c2cca0a1_12874fd5",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 137,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-23T21:35:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: there are two contexts here: ctx and req.Context, which makes this function somewhat not self-contained because it partially assumes that req.Context \u003d\u003d ctx.\nFor example, if someone creates a new context for send() and cancels it, it won\u0027t cancel the request.\n\nI recommend moving newRequest() call to send(), before retry.Retry call",
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6b3992e7_9893700c",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/artifact_uploader.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 137,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-24T23:26:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s a good point. However, I made a change to pass req.Context() to retry.Retry() instead.\n\nif newRequest() is moved inside send(), then send() needs to take params for each of GetBody and ContentLength separately. Passing req.Context() to retry.Retry() seems simpler.",
      "parentUuid": "c2cca0a1_12874fd5",
      "revId": "703e004cf80296ba86af00a458dc07080a646505",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
